ent_completed":0},"active_lock_reason":null,"draft":false,"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/56409","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/56409","diff_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/56409.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/56409.patch","merged_at":null},"body":"This is a further extension to #56128 to make the compiler into a proper stdlib, useable outside of `Base` as `using Compiler` in the same way that `JuliaSyntax` works already. There's a few remaining questions around how loading works, but mechanically, this PR is complete. For those remaining questions, I'll probably put up a separate PR that would migrate JuliaSyntax to it and then simply adopt that here once we've figured out the correct semantics.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/56409/reactions","total_count":15,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":8,"rocket":7,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/56409/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/comments/2457823038","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/56409#issuecomment-2457823038","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/56409","id":2457823038,"node_id":"IC_kwDOABkWpM6Sf2c-","user":{"login":"Keno","id":1291671,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyOTE2NzE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1291671?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Keno","html_url":"https://github.com/Keno","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Keno/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Keno/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Keno/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Keno/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Keno/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Keno/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Keno/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Keno/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Keno/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2024-11-05T17:52:53Z","updated_at":"2024-11-05T17:52:53Z","author_association":"MEMBER","body":"Alright, some further discussion with various folks.

1. @JeffBezanson and @vtjnash don't like the auto-switching of reflection functions, so the compromise is to make the reflection functions always use the (world-age protected) compiler that's currently being used to compile code. Then, there'll be an explicit opt-in to switch it to the loaded compiler. I will very explicitly note that this is not what happens now where `code_typed` always uses the current-world age compiler.

2. On `stdpkg`, @JeffBezanson is fine with top-level, with an eventual goal of doing `base`->`Base` (and possibly splitting out `Core`), moving the `julia` repository to essentially be a mono-repo of packages that happen to be co-developed in it. I personally don't care either way. I'll move it to the toplevel.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/comments/2457823038/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null}}

